# Git Workflow

## Conventional Commits

Use conventional commit format: `type(scope): description`

**Types**: `feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `style` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `ci` | `chore`

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
feat(ai): add streaming support for chat endpoint
fix(api): handle missing API key gracefully
docs(readme): add setup instructions for AI package
refactor(ui): extract ChatWidget into reusable component
chore(deps): bump @biomejs/biome to 1.9.0

# ❌ BAD
Added streaming
fixed bug
WIP
```

## Branch Naming

```
feature/*  - New features (feature/ai-streaming, feature/chat-widget)
fix/*      - Bug fixes (fix/rate-limit-429, fix/api-key-validation)
chore/*    - Maintenance (chore/update-deps, chore/biome-config)
```

## PR Template

PRs should include:

1. **Description** — What changed and why
2. **Test plan** — How to verify (manual steps, tests run)

```markdown
## Description
Adds streaming support to the chat API using Vercel AI SDK streamText().

## Test Plan
- [ ] Run `pnpm test` — all pass
- [ ] Start dev server, call POST /api/ai/chat with valid messages
- [ ] Verify SSE stream returns chunks
```

## Merge Strategy

- **Squash merge** to `main` — keep history clean
- **Rebase** before merge when requested
- **No WIP commits** to main — all commits should be complete

## Atomic Commits

Each commit should be a single logical change.

```bash
# ✅ GOOD - Separate commits
feat(ai): add createChatStream
fix(ai): handle missing provider in getModel
docs(ai): add README with usage

# ❌ BAD - Mixed concerns
feat: add ai stuff and fix docs
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Branch name follows convention
- [ ] Commit messages use conventional format
- [ ] PR has description and test plan
- [ ] No WIP or broken commits
- [ ] Squash merge to main
